00:00:39.640 --> 00:01:05.979
I 

00:01:05.979 --> 00:01:27.540
see many more New Zealanders, very happy to
see all of you here.

00:01:27.540 --> 00:01:31.960
Today I thought we should have Mahasaraswati's
Puja.

00:01:31.960 --> 00:01:40.670
Would be a good idea, because we did Mahalakshmi,
let's have Mahasaraswati.

00:01:40.670 --> 00:01:51.940
So, Mahasaraswati Principle is on the right
side as you all know.

00:01:51.940 --> 00:02:02.200
First is the Brahmadeva's Principle, which
is the Saraswati Principle, and then this

00:02:02.200 --> 00:02:14.989
Mahasaraswati takes you to the principle of
Mahabramadeva called as Hiranyagarba.

00:02:14.989 --> 00:02:24.560
Now this Hiranyagarba Principle, is very important
for Sahaja Yogis.

00:02:24.560 --> 00:02:37.000
First of all, those who think too much or
those who create too much without realization,

00:02:37.000 --> 00:02:52.061
those who express themselves in poetry or
in literature or in music, you can say, in

00:02:52.061 --> 00:03:01.980
paintings, in all kinds of arts; if they are
not realized souls, then they go to the left

00:03:01.980 --> 00:03:03.980
to the extreme or to the right.

00:03:03.980 --> 00:03:16.170
So for example if there is an artist, if he
goes to the right gradually his paintings

00:03:16.170 --> 00:03:24.650
will become extremely violent expressions.

00:03:24.650 --> 00:03:40.049
Would be very much showing something very
violent and also rather, I would say he would

00:03:40.049 --> 00:03:43.180
be a man who would be inflexible.

00:03:43.180 --> 00:03:48.400
He'll have his own style; he can't move into
another style.

00:03:48.400 --> 00:03:54.730
He'll use the same style and he will not get
into any other style.

00:03:54.730 --> 00:04:07.700
Kind of a austere nature he develops in his
productions and then when he gets tired of

00:04:07.700 --> 00:04:17.220
it, then he will take to something you can
say like abstract art but without realization

00:04:17.220 --> 00:04:24.250
the abstract art can be something very absurd
and funny.

00:04:24.250 --> 00:04:34.070
I have seen the extremes of it that I've seen
people who put big canvases on the ground

00:04:34.070 --> 00:04:43.460
and poured lots of oil paints one after another
and roll over it, is supposed to be a painting.

00:04:43.460 --> 00:04:49.800
They say this is spontaneous because they
fell on it or they rolled on that so is spontaneous

00:04:49.800 --> 00:04:52.430
painting that's come out.

00:04:52.430 --> 00:04:59.190
Now this spontaneous painting should come
from a spontaneous personality not by rolling

00:04:59.190 --> 00:05:05.080
on thing or something, I mean, all sorts of
things they do but there's no end to it to

00:05:05.080 --> 00:05:07.969
which nonsensical things they think of.

00:05:07.969 --> 00:05:12.070
And they think they have achieved a lot and
they've done a lot and also they sell it to

00:05:12.070 --> 00:05:15.750
people who have too much of right side.

00:05:15.750 --> 00:05:20.640
They like it.

00:05:20.640 --> 00:05:30.640
So, they put in lot of effort to create this
kind of a painting.

00:05:30.640 --> 00:05:36.570
Also that today's pop music also, which is
very aggressive, is from the same outcome

00:05:36.570 --> 00:05:41.979
because you cannot ascend, so you move to
your right.

00:05:41.979 --> 00:05:48.150
And this pop music then starts now it's becoming
so horribly noisy, I don't know what to call

00:05:48.150 --> 00:05:49.150
it.

00:05:49.150 --> 00:05:56.901
Absolutely it can deafen your ears if you
listen to it and the whole thing is, the whole

00:05:56.901 --> 00:06:03.980
gestures and all that are so ugly and so aggressive
as if they're going to eat the mike sometimes

00:06:03.980 --> 00:06:08.229
I feel the way go on with the mike and things.

00:06:08.229 --> 00:06:15.060
And see then these people also impress such
people who are very right-sided and so they

00:06:15.060 --> 00:06:16.700
become popular.

00:06:16.700 --> 00:06:20.830
But the popularity is not the sign of real
success.

00:06:20.830 --> 00:06:23.490
It will come and go away.

00:06:23.490 --> 00:06:32.890
All such artists and painters come and go
away they have no, no standing, they are there

00:06:32.890 --> 00:06:34.950
for a short time.

00:06:34.950 --> 00:06:40.780
And then the history talks about them those
who have been in the center never about the

00:06:40.780 --> 00:06:42.780
people who went to the extremes.

00:06:42.780 --> 00:06:45.260
God knows how many must have come and gone.

00:06:45.260 --> 00:06:50.350
And those who are today also painting or singing
in that way tomorrow they will not be known.

00:06:50.350 --> 00:06:55.229
One after another you see the craze comes
in one comes and goes away another so they

00:06:55.229 --> 00:07:00.880
are crazy people and they create a craze and
the crazy like them enjoy the craze.

00:07:00.880 --> 00:07:09.690
So it amounts to something that is just wasteful
creates no impression in the history.

00:07:09.690 --> 00:07:17.930
So this is the right-sided nonsense that comes
out of the right side movement of the sympathetic

00:07:17.930 --> 00:07:25.440
going too far with your creativity and also
your writing.

00:07:25.440 --> 00:07:30.200
And there were many writers in English language
you know from Shakespeare you can start who

00:07:30.200 --> 00:07:39.140
showed the futility of human endeavor like
we call an avaduta, the one who has reached

00:07:39.140 --> 00:07:44.520
a very great degree of development in his
spiritual life.

00:07:44.520 --> 00:07:51.219
He can see the futility of human endeavor
and then he brings them to the point that

00:07:51.219 --> 00:07:58.740
they have to rise above these stupid and human
endeavors and take to some sort of an endeavor,

00:07:58.740 --> 00:08:05.610
which will bring them something higher and
also will create something of an eternal value.

00:08:05.610 --> 00:08:11.050
Then also we have, I think in English language
I have said, [INAUDIBLE] to Somerset Maugham

