the road and even if you want to find out
the road and you knock at the door and request

00:10:15.330 --> 00:10:20.380
them that you would like know some road and
all that, they're all drunk already at seven

00:10:20.380 --> 00:10:21.470
o'clock.

00:10:21.470 --> 00:10:28.370
So with this thing they become extremely over-romantic
type and they sing songs of romance, have

00:10:28.370 --> 00:10:34.010
no romance in their life you see, they just,
some sort of a imaginary romance they have

00:10:34.010 --> 00:10:39.890
and they live in that imaginary world of pain
and sufferings and they have their own ideas

00:10:39.890 --> 00:10:48.250
about their own romantic models that they
formed in their heads you see with their left

00:10:48.250 --> 00:10:49.250
side.

00:10:49.250 --> 00:10:54.330
So the poets and the writers go to the left
side like that and in say for example in our

00:10:54.330 --> 00:11:02.210
India we had those Muslims used to drink a
lot then they started a thing called as gazal

00:11:02.210 --> 00:11:04.050
and that gazal is nothing but crying.

00:11:04.050 --> 00:11:09.320
Even in certain poets you see, we have this
kind of a thing in the other places where

00:11:09.320 --> 00:11:14.600
there were many poets who were seeking God
and were crying, "Oh God, when will I meet?"

00:11:14.600 --> 00:11:23.140
and in separation they are singing, not in
the meeting, not in the yoga but in separation

00:11:23.140 --> 00:11:26.170
they sing, 'When will I meet You, oh God?"
and all that.

00:11:26.170 --> 00:11:29.950
And all such people who are still seeking
like such songs going on.

00:11:29.950 --> 00:11:35.540
Up to this much is all right but then you
get lots of grotesque type of writers also

00:11:35.540 --> 00:11:40.560
who write such horrible things that you feel
you are in hell the way they describe things

00:11:40.560 --> 00:11:42.070
are horrible.

00:11:42.070 --> 00:11:45.350
And in Sanskrit called as vivastera create
a vivasaras.

00:11:45.350 --> 00:11:52.280
And it's the description of very filthy things
which were never before even in English language.

00:11:52.280 --> 00:12:04.630
Never I saw that but now some books are full
of filth and dirt and horrible sex descriptions

00:12:04.630 --> 00:12:06.840
that you just can't bear it.

00:12:06.840 --> 00:12:14.710
So all this comes with the left side movement
that, because you see society also moves from

00:12:14.710 --> 00:12:17.870
sometimes to the right sometimes to the left.

00:12:17.870 --> 00:12:22.320
So when it moves to the right they like right-sided
things sometimes they move to the left they

00:12:22.320 --> 00:12:23.710
like left-sided things.

00:12:23.710 --> 00:12:29.160
So also there are people with two types of
temperaments so that's how they start appreciating

00:12:29.160 --> 00:12:33.950
these things and unnecessarily they believe
that they are tragic.

00:12:33.950 --> 00:12:40.250
As you know about the Greek tragedy which
is a very sort of a fundamental thing I would

00:12:40.250 --> 00:12:48.710
say for a Western literature is a Greek tragedy
where a woman marries a man but she doesn't

00:12:48.710 --> 00:12:52.420
love her husband so she loves somebody else
and that tragedy is there.

00:12:52.420 --> 00:12:59.170
I mean it's artificially created tragedy that
shows that you are married to some man and

00:12:59.170 --> 00:13:00.660
you should be happy with him.

00:13:00.660 --> 00:13:04.750
Of course I mean if the man is very bad and
troublesome and all that then you can give

00:13:04.750 --> 00:13:05.750
him up.

00:13:05.750 --> 00:13:09.230
But what's the use of pining for another man,
living with one other man?

00:13:09.230 --> 00:13:14.450
Sort of a thing as you must have heard about
Tolstoy who was another great ralized soul.

00:13:14.450 --> 00:13:19.160
He's written Anna Karenina and ultimately
he saw that Anna Karenina commits suicide.

00:13:19.160 --> 00:13:23.710
Because what she was doing a wrong thing you
see, so he brought the whole thing so beautifully

00:13:23.710 --> 00:13:30.540
out and such an introspection all the time
you see going on and also the futility of

00:13:30.540 --> 00:13:33.490
this kind of a romance that was there.

00:13:33.490 --> 00:13:41.380
So all this shows to us that there are people
at the same time who are in the center I would

00:13:41.380 --> 00:13:47.950
say in French writers also Maupassant was
one of them whom I would put in the center.

00:13:47.950 --> 00:13:52.040
He showed both the sides and he showed the
right side also.

00:13:52.040 --> 00:13:59.920
So we have had Goethe, we had many sort of
people in Europe and England also in English

00:13:59.920 --> 00:14:02.880
language because I am talking about English
language.

00:14:02.880 --> 00:14:08.900
But also same in Sanskrit, in Hindi, in every
language we have the same type of people but

00:14:08.900 --> 00:14:10.950
more in Sanskrit.

00:14:10.950 --> 00:14:16.210
We don't have many people with this right
or left side.

00:14:16.210 --> 00:14:19.870
The reason is: for literature there are some
rules and regulations.

00:14:19.870 --> 00:14:27.300
It's not the Western idea in India that we
should be abandoned people.

00:14:27.300 --> 00:14:29.230
That's not accepted.

00:14:29.230 --> 00:14:33.540
So even in literature there is a kind of a
restriction.

00:14:33.540 --> 00:14:37.020
What is a literature?

00:14:37.020 --> 00:14:40.200
Sahitya, it's called as sahit, means which
will be benevolent.

00:14:40.200 --> 00:14:44.160
Sahita means which will be benevolent.

00:14:44.160 --> 00:14:48.550
If it is not benevolent then it is not sahitya,
it's not literature.

00:14:48.550 --> 00:14:50.050
Then it is trash.

00:14:50.050 --> 00:14:57.710
So that restriction you see, which is there
which is given to us by great saints and seers,

00:14:57.710 --> 00:14:59.600
is still accepted.

00:14:59.600 --> 00:15:05.089
Of course, some people deviate a little bit,
little bit they deviate, but once they deviate

00:15:05.089 --> 00:15:11.000
it goes out of the society, people just don't
read it.

00:15:11.000 --> 00:15:16.010
Say for example some people must have written
this Karma Sutra or something long time back

00:15:16.010 --> 00:15:20.460
but we never knew about it, we never read
about it till the Germans came and made such

00:15:20.460 --> 00:15:23.610
an ado out of it, we never knew there are
such books.

00:15:23.610 --> 00:15:27.540
Even now I don't know who wrote it or I've
never read such a book, I've never seen it

00:15:27.540 --> 00:15:32.400
with My own eyes but we have heard about it
that people wrote such things.

00:15:32.400 --> 00:15:40.010
But actually if you ask a ordinary human being
in India who is maybe a scholar also, he will

00:15:40.010 --> 00:15:41.010
say, "What's that?

00:15:41.010 --> 00:15:42.520
I've never heard about it."

00:15:42.520 --> 00:15:48.310
But the Germans or the Japanese very particular
on these things, they want to find all such

00:15:48.310 --> 00:15:49.310
things.

00:15:49.310 --> 00:16:00.529
So these creations of ugliness I should say,
or of vulgarity, all these are a compensation

00:16:00.529 --> 00:16:08.240
for people who are very right-sided also because
a right-sided man will always take to drink.

00:16:08.240 --> 00:16:14.360
Because you see he wants to compensate so
the right-sided man also will like such horrible

00:16:14.360 --> 00:16:23.010
things just to quench his thirst for power
you see.

00:16:23.010 --> 00:16:31.770
He's so mad and then he would like to little
bit neutralize that movement in such a way

00:16:31.770 --> 00:16:38.970
that his right-sided behavior is little bit
compensated by the left side.

00:16:38.970 --> 00:16:42.620
So the people who are right-sided take to
drinks very much.

00:16:42.620 --> 00:16:49.210
You will see people will work very hard and
two nights, Saturday and Sunday night, they're

00:16:49.210 --> 00:16:50.210
just drunk.

00:16:50.210 --> 00:16:53.339
Then Monday they'll come out with a hangover.

00:16:53.339 --> 00:16:56.220
See it's very interesting to note how human
being are.

00:16:56.220 --> 00:17:01.430
For five days they will slog, slog, slog,
slog, slog and then two days they'll just

00:17:01.430 --> 00:17:06.770
go into a kind of a hibernation as they say
and absolutely lost to the whole world.

00:17:06.770 --> 00:17:10.689
Whether they are doctors or professionals,
they don't care.

00:17:10.689 --> 00:17:14.550
So whatever they earn in five days they'll
spend it in these two days in drinking and

00:17:14.550 --> 00:17:15.880
finish it off.

00:17:15.880 --> 00:17:28.439
So that's how the total gain in all that creativity
comes in.

00:17:28.439 --> 00:17:42.510
Now, when these extreme things start showing
results and then the artist gets just fed

00:17:42.510 --> 00:17:49.720
up with this kind of thing going on all round
he sees and all that.

00:17:49.720 --> 00:17:59.060
Then within him rises a subtler attitude towards
creativity, towards art, towards books and

00:17:59.060 --> 00:18:07.680
all that and then he starts in that, reading
about the true knowledge pure knowledge.

00:18:07.680 --> 00:18:18.840
He wants to see paintings or he wants to listen
to music which sings of Divine or divinity.

00:18:18.840 --> 00:18:29.660
Whole that madness makes him really think
that now we should start doing something better

00:18:29.660 --> 00:18:33.410
and then the Mahasaraswati Principle starts
working out.

00:18:33.410 --> 00:18:40.140
But in that also when they start thinking
of God, they fall into traps.

00:18:40.140 --> 00:18:43.590
Like you see somebody might fall into some
sort of a religion.

00:18:43.590 --> 00:18:49.680
Now as you know these religions so-called
are just money-oriented or power-oriented.

00:18:49.680 --> 00:18:52.990
They are not at all in no way spirit-oriented.

00:18:52.990 --> 00:19:00.620
That's the reason when they are not spirit-oriented
what they give people is a kind of a personality

00:19:00.620 --> 00:19:04.280
which is all mental.

00:19:04.280 --> 00:19:11.230
You ask them about Upanishads they will recite
verses after verses.

00:19:11.230 --> 00:19:14.870
Gita they'll give big lectures on that hours
together.

00:19:14.870 --> 00:19:19.520
For this Chinmoy you see if you hear him,
he speaks for hours together on Gita you get

00:19:19.520 --> 00:19:20.772
tired and bored stiff with his lectures.

00:19:20.772 --> 00:19:25.640
He can speak about it but nothing inside.

00:19:25.640 --> 00:19:30.000
Nothing inside and whatever they speak has
no effect on others also because they are

00:19:30.000 --> 00:19:36.300
not awakened people, they are not connected
with the Divine and whatever they do is just

00:19:36.300 --> 00:19:37.300
mental.

00:19:37.300 --> 00:19:44.320
So when the Mahasaraswati Principle is awakened
you start seeing it clearly that "This is

00:19:44.320 --> 00:19:49.100
mental, this is not the truth, there must
be something higher."

00:19:49.100 --> 00:20:02.650
They read about all the spiritual works in
their own religion in which they are born,

00:20:02.650 --> 00:20:07.000
then they start moving out and reading about
some other religions also.

00:20:07.000 --> 00:20:12.370
Then this thing that every religion says the
same thing then it comes to the Agnya point.

00:20:12.370 --> 00:20:19.830
When it comes to the Agnya point only there
then suddenly they realize that there is something

00:20:19.830 --> 00:20:26.060
wrong, that people are mentally only accepting
this religion and there must be something

00:20:26.060 --> 00:20:28.300
beyond this.

00:20:28.300 --> 00:20:35.430
At that point if somebody gets the realization,
he just takes to it.

00:20:35.430 --> 00:20:41.290
But this Mahasaraswati Principle has to be
awakened in all the people who are musicians,who

00:20:41.290 --> 00:20:45.400
are artists, who are this and that and that.

00:20:45.400 --> 00:20:50.400
And those who have reached that state, then
suddenly they can get realization very easily.

00:20:50.400 --> 00:20:56.200
I've seen some people, very great artists
they are today but when they came to Me first

00:20:56.200 --> 00:20:58.400
were not at all well known or anything.

00:20:58.400 --> 00:21:02.980
But when they came to Me while singing only
they got their realization just singing.

00:21:02.980 --> 00:21:10.690
Or there was one gentleman who was just playing
tabla before Me, I mean not so good, all right,

00:21:10.690 --> 00:21:19.179
and then I was in Pune where I saw him, and
in Pune he was playing very well and I said,

00:21:19.179 --> 00:21:20.780
"He's the same fellow."

00:21:20.780 --> 00:21:25.230
But somebody said, "No, no, Mother, he's not
the same, he was not such a great player."

00:21:25.230 --> 00:21:26.230
I said, "All right."

00:21:26.230 --> 00:21:29.280
I had taken some flowers for these musicians
so I sent it.

00:21:29.280 --> 00:21:30.840
He came running and touched My feet.

00:21:30.840 --> 00:21:32.690
"Mother, have you not recognized me or what?"

00:21:32.690 --> 00:21:34.770
I said, "I have, that's why I have brought
you the flowers."

00:21:34.770 --> 00:21:36.179
I didn't know what to say.

00:21:36.179 --> 00:21:39.270
But the way he had improved, now he is a world
famous tabla player, world famous.

00:21:39.270 --> 00:21:46.679
It has happened with many others also the
sarod people with the sitar people, so many

00:21:46.679 --> 00:21:49.350
people have achieved a lot.

00:21:49.350 --> 00:22:00.310
Musicians they after coming to Me they have
asked Me that "Please, do something that we

00:22:00.310 --> 00:22:05.010
should be able to enhance our creativity."

00:22:05.010 --> 00:22:08.830
I just said, "Take to Sahaj, that's all."

00:22:08.830 --> 00:22:15.700
And when they were awakened very surprisingly
today most of them are very well known musicians

00:22:15.700 --> 00:22:18.700
and very famous in India.

