till they the way they are screaming these
days I think their throats will be out may

00:22:27.950 --> 00:22:30.440
be something then they might come to Me.

00:22:30.440 --> 00:22:45.750
But on the whole My own idea is this, that
those who have reached Mahasaraswati level

00:22:45.750 --> 00:22:55.080
through reading or through creativity, but
through writings or anything, when they reach

00:22:55.080 --> 00:23:06.730
a certain state of Agnya, then either they
get disappointed go to the left and absolutely

00:23:06.730 --> 00:23:08.800
think that this is all useless.

00:23:08.800 --> 00:23:19.679
Or else if they get realization they become
really very dynamic artists, very dynamic

00:23:19.679 --> 00:23:28.140
writers and people who are creating something
of an eternal value.

00:23:28.140 --> 00:23:34.950
So many Sahaja Yogis who have never spoken
on the stage, who have never been on the stage

00:23:34.950 --> 00:23:37.410
they said, "We had a fright for the stage."

00:23:37.410 --> 00:23:46.340
They all, surprisingly now have become great
orators and speak very well and know so much.

00:23:46.340 --> 00:23:49.670
So this is the Mahasaraswati Principle.

00:23:49.670 --> 00:23:57.740
Now this makes you a person much subtler and
you start becoming aware that the gross understanding

00:23:57.740 --> 00:24:08.800
we had about our art or our creativity has
to be subtler, we have to be subtler people.

00:24:08.800 --> 00:24:13.610
And then such writers only appeal to people
who are subtler.

00:24:13.610 --> 00:24:16.970
Like William Blake was regarded as a mad poet.

00:24:16.970 --> 00:24:19.650
I mean in India I never read about him.

00:24:19.650 --> 00:24:25.610
I did read on My own but in the colleges university
they never had William Blake or in any book

00:24:25.610 --> 00:24:28.150
as such there was no William Blake.

00:24:28.150 --> 00:24:36.140
But when you go to these people and talk to
them, there was one called Mascaro fellow,

00:24:36.140 --> 00:24:44.540
he has translated Gita into English, is a
very wonderful person.

00:24:44.540 --> 00:24:46.580
He is, actually I think he is a Italian.

00:24:46.580 --> 00:24:48.309
Now he is no more.

00:24:48.309 --> 00:24:50.030
He lived in near Cambridge.

00:24:50.030 --> 00:24:58.630
I went to see him, he was very anxious to
meet Me and when I went there you'll be amazed,

00:24:58.630 --> 00:25:07.640
he did My aarti, and he said a mantra in Sanskrit
that "Oh God, You have come to my house!

00:25:07.640 --> 00:25:12.910
What have I done in my previous lives that
You are in my house?"

00:25:12.910 --> 00:25:21.710
Such a beautiful poet, you see, and he said
in Sanskrit language, he was a master of Sanskrit.

00:25:21.710 --> 00:25:25.270
So I asked him, "From which book you have
taken this couplet?"

00:25:25.270 --> 00:25:27.810
He said, "I've composed it myself."

00:25:27.810 --> 00:25:32.110
So beautiful it was, and then he said certain
things from Gita and all that.

00:25:32.110 --> 00:25:34.799
And he said, "Mother, I don't know You might
be ..."

00:25:34.799 --> 00:25:36.100
He was very old that time.

00:25:36.100 --> 00:25:37.530
He was eighty years of age.

00:25:37.530 --> 00:25:43.790
He said, "Mother, maybe You might be able
to change these English, but I don't think

00:25:43.790 --> 00:25:45.110
I've done anything.

00:25:45.110 --> 00:25:48.040
Even when I translated Gita they are just
reading only.

00:25:48.040 --> 00:25:49.470
Reading Gita, that's all.

00:25:49.470 --> 00:25:51.630
So what's the use of my translation?

00:25:51.630 --> 00:25:52.630
Just like Bible.

00:25:52.630 --> 00:25:54.130
Now they are reading word by word Gita.

00:25:54.130 --> 00:25:55.130
So, finished!

00:25:55.130 --> 00:25:56.660
What's the use of doing this work?"

00:25:56.660 --> 00:25:59.330
And he was so disappointed with the whole
thing.

00:25:59.330 --> 00:26:01.640
So he said, "What will You work out?

00:26:01.640 --> 00:26:03.200
How will You work out?"

00:26:03.200 --> 00:26:05.080
I said, "All right, I'll try."

00:26:05.080 --> 00:26:08.059
He said, "Of course, You are there; You are
an Incarnation."

00:26:08.059 --> 00:26:09.380
He just recognized Me.

00:26:09.380 --> 00:26:11.320
"I know You'll work it out."

00:26:11.320 --> 00:26:16.220
He wrote a very nice letter to Me also and
then he died.

00:26:16.220 --> 00:26:20.130
But such a nice man and he suffered a lot.

00:26:20.130 --> 00:26:21.640
Nobody tried to understand him.

00:26:21.640 --> 00:26:27.460
He said, "I talked to so many scientists and
things and they're absolutely useless and

00:26:27.460 --> 00:26:29.320
very superficial.

00:26:29.320 --> 00:26:34.240
So I don't think in this country of England
You'll be able to do much, is a very superficial

00:26:34.240 --> 00:26:35.240
country."

00:26:35.240 --> 00:26:40.130
There were at least twenty English Sahaja
Yogis with Me sitting there listening to it.

00:26:40.130 --> 00:26:44.840
He said, "They are extremely superficial,
this language is superficial, they don't know

00:26:44.840 --> 00:26:48.010
about anything about Spirit or anything about
Kundalini."

00:26:48.010 --> 00:26:57.040
And he was a very well read man very deep
person and he told Me that while he was studying

00:26:57.040 --> 00:27:02.120
gradually he felt this Mahasaraswati Principle
the way he didn't say Mahasaraswati but he

00:27:02.120 --> 00:27:05.200
felt there must be subtler knowledge subtler
knowledge.

00:27:05.200 --> 00:27:11.840
So he took to books like Gita, this, that,
and then suddenly he felt that it's all reading

00:27:11.840 --> 00:27:12.840
again.

00:27:12.840 --> 00:27:18.299
It's just the same like translation and specially
when he translated Gita he was amazed that

00:27:18.299 --> 00:27:23.600
people were just reading it like Bible then.

00:27:23.600 --> 00:27:30.470
Then he said that "Mother, I don't know how
but one day I was praying to Mother Mary and

00:27:30.470 --> 00:27:33.350
to the Holy Ghost and I got my realization."

00:27:33.350 --> 00:27:37.660
So he was a realized soul and he saw Me in
dream, you see.

00:27:37.660 --> 00:27:40.140
He said, "In dream You came and gave me realization."

00:27:40.140 --> 00:27:41.140
It's surprising.

00:27:41.140 --> 00:27:42.950
He saw Me in dream and he got ...

00:27:42.950 --> 00:27:46.290
There's another few people who have got it,
but specially him.

00:27:46.290 --> 00:27:49.900
I was so surprised so when I arrived in his
house he recognized Me immediately.

00:27:49.900 --> 00:27:52.020
He said, " I saw You in my dream.

00:27:52.020 --> 00:27:56.650
You came and gave me realization, You awakened
my Kundalini and You gave me realization."

00:27:56.650 --> 00:28:04.600
So you can imagine that this gentleman was
so beautifully placed so subtle, he was that

00:28:04.600 --> 00:28:05.760
at the Agnya point.

00:28:05.760 --> 00:28:08.670
He just got the dream and he got realization.

00:28:08.670 --> 00:28:13.120
And he said, "All the knowledge is now revealed
to me so much more."

00:28:13.120 --> 00:28:15.150
And then he sat down with Me.

00:28:15.150 --> 00:28:16.820
And he said, "Can you stay for some time?"

00:28:16.820 --> 00:28:18.289
I said, "I am now going away."

00:28:18.289 --> 00:28:21.039
But at least for five hours he was talking
to Me.

00:28:21.039 --> 00:28:23.730
He was not tired, he would not leave Me.

00:28:23.730 --> 00:28:25.790
Such an old man was sitting at My feet.

00:28:25.790 --> 00:28:28.640
I was telling him, "You sit on the chair."

00:28:28.640 --> 00:28:29.640
"'No, I'm very good.

00:28:29.640 --> 00:28:31.780
I'm very much all right You sitting there."

00:28:31.780 --> 00:28:36.679
So this is what happens with this Mahasaraswati
Principle developing within us.

00:28:36.679 --> 00:28:39.850
But we should allow that to grow within us.

00:28:39.850 --> 00:28:43.999
So in Sahaja Yoga we are not told that we
are not to read any book, not at all.

00:28:43.999 --> 00:28:49.370
We have to read, but in that book we have
to see the subtle points and see for yourself.

00:28:49.370 --> 00:28:53.260
I don't read any scriptures, because I don't
need to read.

00:28:53.260 --> 00:28:59.270
But when I started reading the, you see, these
intellectuals, what they have to say, I was

00:28:59.270 --> 00:29:01.580
amazed that they are saying the same thing.

00:29:01.580 --> 00:29:02.910
There's nothing new.

00:29:02.910 --> 00:29:06.810
What I know, what I say, that's what they
are saying.

00:29:06.810 --> 00:29:10.950
There's nothing new about it; there's nothing
special about it.

00:29:10.950 --> 00:29:15.140
Just what all the scriptures have said, they
have said the same thing, and these people

00:29:15.140 --> 00:29:17.240
are saying the same thing.

00:29:17.240 --> 00:29:20.180
But by saying these things, how are they going
to propagate?

00:29:20.180 --> 00:29:21.180
Nothing.

00:29:21.180 --> 00:29:29.799
It will be just again something that will
happen outside and it will drop out.

00:29:29.799 --> 00:29:34.840
It doesn't become part and part of yourself,
so it has to become innate.

00:29:34.840 --> 00:29:39.370
That's only possible if your Spirit comes
into your attention.

00:29:39.370 --> 00:29:41.490
There's no other way out.

00:29:41.490 --> 00:29:48.059
So luckily you all are realized souls and
your Mahasaraswati is very much there, but

00:29:48.059 --> 00:29:49.670
I would say you must read.

00:29:49.670 --> 00:29:57.539
Read books of value and understand how it
is absolute Sahaja Yoga there, how it is there.

00:29:57.539 --> 00:30:03.420
Anything you take up you'll be surprised that
all these books are talking about Sahaja Yoga.

00:30:03.420 --> 00:30:07.620
May not be all of it, but part of the Sahaja
Yoga is there.

00:30:07.620 --> 00:30:12.660
All of them talk of some part of Sahaja Yoga
but not the whole of it, because they came

00:30:12.660 --> 00:30:14.190
at different times.

00:30:14.190 --> 00:30:18.850
And now the Sahaja Yoga is the time when you
have to know the complete, integrated knowledge

00:30:18.850 --> 00:30:24.400
of this religious thought that was there.

00:30:24.400 --> 00:30:25.470
Complete integrated.

00:30:25.470 --> 00:30:29.660
And that's how you understand that all religions
are integrated.

00:30:29.660 --> 00:30:33.460
So one should, in Sahaja Yoga, after you come,
people don't take to any reading.

00:30:33.460 --> 00:30:34.460
Is a wrong thing.

00:30:34.460 --> 00:30:40.720
They should read and understand what others
have said, where have they gone wrong.

00:30:40.720 --> 00:30:42.740
But not these nonsensical people.

00:30:42.740 --> 00:30:46.760
You shouldn't read these nonsensical people
which you know are nonsensical.

00:30:46.760 --> 00:30:51.950
But so many, the other day I got this book
of the Christian Science.

00:30:51.950 --> 00:30:54.179
It's all Bible nothing special about it.

00:30:54.179 --> 00:30:58.700
They are saying you should not do this; you
should not do this, and all that.

00:30:58.700 --> 00:31:00.430
It's all written in the Bible.

00:31:00.430 --> 00:31:02.850
What new things are you telling?

00:31:02.850 --> 00:31:03.850
Nothing.

00:31:03.850 --> 00:31:04.850
You don't need a science for that.

00:31:04.850 --> 00:31:06.300
It's just there.

00:31:06.300 --> 00:31:11.720
But they are making money out of it by explaining
and this and this.

00:31:11.720 --> 00:31:12.820
No explanation needed.

00:31:12.820 --> 00:31:17.780
Because that has to come within yourself is
the point which is not there.

00:31:17.780 --> 00:31:23.600
So now, this Mahaswaraswati Principle is awakened
within us and we have to read and see the

00:31:23.600 --> 00:31:33.660
subtle side of this growth of thought, how
it grew up and how it became subtler and subtler,

00:31:33.660 --> 00:31:37.600
and how so many people in the world have contributed
to it.

00:31:37.600 --> 00:31:46.640
So many artists, so many musicians and so
many, we can say, writers who have really

00:31:46.640 --> 00:31:53.650
contributed to the central path of Sushumna
because they became realized souls.

00:31:53.650 --> 00:31:55.280
They were realized souls.

00:31:55.280 --> 00:32:02.190
Some were born, and some became, and then
they completely wrote about the yoga.

00:32:02.190 --> 00:32:08.010
For example Rabindranath Tagore, in the beginning
he writes, "How, when will I meet you my friend?"

00:32:08.010 --> 00:32:09.720
and all that.

00:32:09.720 --> 00:32:13.059
What you call the separation song, [INAUDIBLE]
yoga.

00:32:13.059 --> 00:32:18.419
And then after some time, suddenly he gets
his realization, because he becomes subtler

00:32:18.419 --> 00:32:20.080
and subtler and subtler.

00:32:20.080 --> 00:32:28.309
Then he writes about his meeting, his meeting
the Spirit and he writes about it.

00:32:28.309 --> 00:32:36.130
So these things work out in such a manner
for some people that by their subtleties they

00:32:36.130 --> 00:32:38.510
arrive at a point of realization.

00:32:38.510 --> 00:32:40.860
Same thing happened with Buddha.

00:32:40.860 --> 00:32:42.380
He did the same thing.

00:32:42.380 --> 00:32:49.480
He renounced everything, renounced His family
went out, read Upanishads this, that.

00:32:49.480 --> 00:32:56.650
Everything He read and ultimately reached
Gaya where He was sleeping under a banyan

00:32:56.650 --> 00:32:57.650
tree.

00:32:57.650 --> 00:33:07.030
And while sleeping only, He was so tired and
fed up, He got his realization.

00:33:07.030 --> 00:33:10.230
And that's what is very important.

00:33:10.230 --> 00:33:14.809
But for the Buddhists what He did before going
there is important.

00:33:14.809 --> 00:33:19.630
So they also want to also renounce this and
become sanyasis, this, that.

00:33:19.630 --> 00:33:21.730
But by becoming that, nothing is going to
happen.

00:33:21.730 --> 00:33:25.539
It's going to Gaya and sleeping there also
won't happen.

00:33:25.539 --> 00:33:33.730
It has to happen because He was a pure seeker,
true seeker and that's why it happened.

00:33:33.730 --> 00:33:38.909
But for Sahaja Yogis, they don't have to do
anything of the kind they just get it, realization.

00:33:38.909 --> 00:33:44.880
Because I think most of them in their last
lives have crossed most of their problems,

00:33:44.880 --> 00:33:47.970
and have known that it's nothing, it's all
nonsense in all these things.

00:33:47.970 --> 00:33:52.429
Or maybe in this life also they must have
realized it's all nonsense.

00:33:52.429 --> 00:33:55.650
And then they must have come to Sahaja Yog.

00:33:55.650 --> 00:34:03.220
So it's a very great luck for you that you
are here and you've got your realization and

00:34:03.220 --> 00:34:11.280
that you are enjoying yourself.

00:34:11.280 --> 00:34:19.220
May God bless you!

00:34:19.220 --> 00:34:24.929
Another side which I have left over is the
political side - on the right side, you see.

00:34:24.929 --> 00:34:32.109
Even in politics, the growth becomes subtler
and subtler.

00:34:32.109 --> 00:34:39.750
Like in say, we can say, in Russia when it
was such a power-oriented thing.

00:34:39.750 --> 00:34:41.149
It's not money-oriented.

00:34:41.149 --> 00:34:46.020
The Communism was so power-oriented it reached
a place that person like Gorbachev was to

00:34:46.020 --> 00:34:54.429
be born who would put it in a proper sense,
and he came on a central path.

00:34:54.429 --> 00:35:00.349
He didn't want complete democracy as it is
in America, it's a demonocracy, but he wanted

00:35:00.349 --> 00:35:02.039
a balanced thing.

00:35:02.039 --> 00:35:06.640
So far he has not been able to manage, but
I'm sure one day he will be managed, but he

00:35:06.640 --> 00:35:17.690
will be known all over the world for his great,
great thought and great work of reducing the

00:35:17.690 --> 00:35:24.309
pressure between the two great, or say between
the two ideologists.

00:35:24.309 --> 00:35:31.660
And he's done such a good thing that now there's
no war, going to be no war, as I mean not

00:35:31.660 --> 00:35:34.579
a very big world war but could be little bit
here and there.

00:35:34.579 --> 00:35:39.539
That also is coming up which is a problem
of fundamentalism, is not due to political

00:35:39.539 --> 00:35:41.220
but fundamentalism.

00:35:41.220 --> 00:35:46.640
So now the problem today is fundamentalism
and that also comes from the right side, absolutely.

00:35:46.640 --> 00:35:53.539
Fundamentalists are all right-sided people
and this right-sidedness takes them to any

00:35:53.539 --> 00:36:00.809
extreme of violence could be or, in some cases,
it's really crazy and madness.

00:36:00.809 --> 00:36:06.660
But a new disease has started now those who
go too much to the right is called as a yuppies

00:36:06.660 --> 00:36:13.500
disease where the whole conscious mind goes
out of order and you become like a reptile.

00:36:13.500 --> 00:36:20.660
I've seen people being carried like big fishes
on the shoulders you see and put in a seat

00:36:20.660 --> 00:36:22.519
and they just know everything.

00:36:22.519 --> 00:36:26.809
By brain is all right but they understand
everything.

00:36:26.809 --> 00:36:33.500
They can talk well but they cannot move their
hands, cannot move their feet if they want

00:36:33.500 --> 00:36:34.500
to.

00:36:34.500 --> 00:36:38.289
Unconsciously they may, but consciously they
cannot, and this disease is the one which

00:36:38.289 --> 00:36:41.960
is a warning to everyone.

00:36:41.960 --> 00:36:46.609
So we have be careful in Sahaja Yoga also,
we should not go too much to the right is

00:36:46.609 --> 00:36:48.109
also very dangerous, too.

00:36:48.109 --> 00:36:54.099
Some people become very fanatic and start
teaching Sahaja Yoga in a very fanatical manner

00:36:54.099 --> 00:36:58.420
and sort of you see, make a ... I don't know
what to call that.

00:36:58.420 --> 00:37:02.940
But sometimes I see some people speaking in
a manner that one should never speak that

00:37:02.940 --> 00:37:05.660
way because we are Sahaja Yogis.

00:37:05.660 --> 00:37:17.390
The main thing is love, compassion, which
is a living force and must be done everything,

00:37:17.390 --> 00:37:29.430
with that force, which is a beautiful, living
force which creates these flowers, which does

00:37:29.430 --> 00:37:32.960
all kinds of beautiful constructive things.

00:37:32.960 --> 00:37:46.180
It should not be in any way a oppression,
domination or in any kind of command.

00:37:46.180 --> 00:37:51.530
You should not do like this, and organization,
nothing of the kind.

00:37:51.530 --> 00:37:57.099
It is something so spontaneous, so beautiful,
just works out.

00:37:57.099 --> 00:38:03.589
But as these trees have to be embedded in
the Mother Earth, in the same way you should

00:38:03.589 --> 00:38:10.599
be embedded in the principle of Sahaja Yoga
which is compassion, love, and divine grace.

00:38:10.599 --> 00:38:15.030
If it is not there, then you'll have problems
with leadership and you'll have problems with

00:38:15.030 --> 00:38:19.279
... Anybody who's a violent person cannot
stay in Sahaja Yoga.

00:38:19.279 --> 00:38:20.299
He has to disappear.

00:38:20.299 --> 00:38:24.239
Either he should change himself entirely or
he has to disappear.

00:38:24.239 --> 00:38:27.490
It doesn't work out with people who are violent.

00:38:27.490 --> 00:38:34.599
So one has to understand that you may be in
any position, you may be anywhere, you may

00:38:34.599 --> 00:38:40.469
be a very poor person, you may be very rich
but makes no difference for a Sahaja Yogi.

00:38:40.469 --> 00:38:48.289
The best thing to judge yourself is that whenever
we are doing anything for anyone or saying

00:38:48.289 --> 00:38:54.719
anything, is it benevolent or is it violent?

00:38:54.719 --> 00:39:10.039
Is it for our self-propagation or self, holier-than-thou
sort of a principle or it is for the goodness

00:39:10.039 --> 00:39:11.839
of others?

00:39:11.839 --> 00:39:19.430
Once you start judging like that, you'll be
amazed that your whole system will change,

00:39:19.430 --> 00:39:23.810
your way of talking, your way of working it
out.

00:39:23.810 --> 00:39:27.069
For example today you see there was a lady
who wouldn't allow Me to talk at all.

00:39:27.069 --> 00:39:30.410
She was talking all the time about something
which was not important.

00:39:30.410 --> 00:39:34.450
But still I was working it out because I knew
that there's no need to talk now.

00:39:34.450 --> 00:39:37.130
With this gentleman I can work it out.

00:39:37.130 --> 00:39:45.609
So it is always so that you should try to
see the whole thing as a complete play and

00:39:45.609 --> 00:40:00.730
take a very, a witness state, in 
a witness state you should watch.

00:40:00.730 --> 00:40:08.859
If you watch everything in a witness state
then you can handle the whole situation very

00:40:08.859 --> 00:40:14.479
nicely, even if you do not talk, if you do
not say anything still in a witness state

00:40:14.479 --> 00:40:58.529
you become very powerful, and in that witness
state you can easily solve lots 

00:40:58.529 --> 00:58:32.420
of problems.

00:58:32.420 --> 02:08:47.850
May God bless you!

